'Ay, little Nan,' he answered; 'for a bit, darling. Please God, we'll go home
                         again some day. But little Nan shall always live with Stevie. That'll do;
                         won't it?'

'But God will never forgive me now,' replied Martha hopelessly; 'I see how
                         wicked I have been, but the chance is gone by. God will not forgive me now;
                         nor Stephen.'
